Formatting date using `SimpleDateFormat` doesn&#39;t support *suffix* 
 (**st**, **nd**, **rd** and **th**) so we have to replace if they are present in the string .

Formatting using SimpleDateFormat
================================

&gt; [SimpleDateFormat][1] is a concrete class for formatting and parsing dates
&gt; in a locale-sensitive manner. It allows for formatting (date -&gt; text),
&gt; parsing (text -&gt; date), and normalization.

