After your edit: the `this` reference is never null, therefore `this == null` will always be false. You need to handle the null-check outside of your class. Normally, `String.valueOf` will be called when converting an object to a string. This method handles `null` references, not the class itself. You&#39;d have to manually convert your object to a string first (with the utility described above).

